        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 11 at 6:24PM MDT until July 11 at 7:00PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>SVRBOU

The National Weather Service in Denver has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
East Central Weld County in northeastern Colorado...

* Until 700 PM MDT.

* At 624 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 10 miles north of
Stoneham, or 30 miles west of Sterling, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Ping pong ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect
hail damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles.
Expect wind damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Mainly rural areas of East Central Weld County.
</description>
        <instruction>Seek shelter inside a well-built structure and stay away from
windows. This storm is capable of producing damaging winds and large
hail.</instruction>
